A nurse is facing a mastectomy after refusing to challenge her doctor's opinion when her concerns over breast cancer were dismissed.

Rika Turner did not want to 'overstep the boundaries' by questioning her GP, despite suspecting something was wrong.

The 38-year-old went to see a doctor last year, after feeling tenderness in her breast.

The mother-of-one from Gloucester was reassured there was nothing sinister to blame, but despite suspecting that was not the case, Ms Turner accepted her doctor's opinion.

