She said she 'didn't want to be a nuisance', and so did not raise doubts.

But months later when she raised the problem with her GP she was referred for a scan, which revealed a cancerous lump in her breast.

She now faces a mastectomy to remove all the breast tissue, to try and stop the disease spreading.

